3. HTTP Methods- GET, POST, PUT, DELETE
.......................
GET   Fetch data. Should never change anything on the server.
POST  Create a new resource. Sends data in the request body.
PUT    Update an existing resource. Replaces the whole thing.
PATCH    Partially update a resource. Just change what you specify.
DELETE     Remove a resource from the server.


4. HTTP Status Codes- What Your API Says Back
...............................

200 OK Everything worked. You're returning data.
201 Created A new resource was successfully created (after POST).
204 No Content Success, but nothing to return (like after DELETE).

400 Bad Request Client sent invalid data. Their fault, not yours.
401 Unauthorized User is not authenticated (not logged in).
403 Forbidden User is authenticated but doesn't have permission.
404 Not Found The resource doesn't exist.
500 Internal Server Error Something broke on the server side. Your fault.


